$interpreted: Wolf Chieftain: They went that way! Get 'em!!
Toyokuni: They're gone.
Shun: Is the arbiter alright?
Jia-Shen: She's not great, her wound is pretty deep. I can slow the bleeding, but we've gotta get 'er to a doctor, stat!
Toyokuni: We have to find a way out of here...
Tindoiimu: ……
TIngko: Princess...
Tindoiimu: Tingko, I'm so glad you're okay.
TIngko: What happened, Princess? All of a sudden there were so many soldiers...
TIngko: And, what were you doing with them?
Tindoiimu: There's no time to explain right now, just stick with me.
Toyokuni: You all go and hide, I'll focus on getting us out of here.
Shun: No, you can't do it alone, it's too risky!
Toyokuni: It's a risk I'm willing to take! Plus, it'll be faster if I act alone.
Tindoiimu: Toyokuni...
Toyokuni: I'll get out of here and have my tribe come back to save you.
Tindoiimu: Save us? Would the Komainu Tribe really agree to help some... insects?
Toyokuni: It doesn't matter what tribe you're from. You won the tournament, and now you're our arbiter.
Toyokuni: Don't worry, I will convince them to help. For now, just hide.
Shun: Stop right there, Toyokuni!
Shun: Quit playing the hero! We're doing this together!
Toyokuni: Shun... Fine, together then.
Toyokuni: Watch over Maeok for me, Tindoiimu.
Bull Chieftain: There they are! Get 'em!
Chiyuki: Let's not waste the opportunity they gave us. Let's go hide.
Tindoiimu: Wait a second... spirit wind!?
Tindoiimu: Tingko...
Tindoiimu: ...Where is everyone?
Tindoiimu: The Honey Badger Tribe!? What are they doing here!?
Qing-Feng: They're our Plan B.
Tindoiimu: Qing-Feng is working together with the honey badgers... of course he is.
Qing-Feng: Hmph, so what?
Tindoiimu: I'm gonna wipe that smug smile right off your face!
Tindoiimu: Hmph... gyagh...
Qing-Feng: Now I can see why you won the tournament. Not bad.
Tindoiimu: I'm strong... mngh... I can take care of myself...
Qing-Feng: You're not just an insect... you're a pest. And I don't need pests in my Alliance.
TIngko: Princess.
Tindoiimu: Stay put, I can handle this.
Beaten Assassin: Gyagh!
Qing-Feng: What the...
Qing-Feng: Get them! Don't let them escape!
Maeok: Gungh... *pant*... I'm too old. Just this little bit of running and I'm so tired...
Tindoiimu: Maeok!? What are you doing here!?
Maeok: I have... unfinished business...
TIngko: Princess, her body is so cold... she's lost a lot of blood!
Tindoiimu: She was hurt bad...
Maeok: That's not important. I have something to give you...
Tindoiimu: What is this?
Maeok: This is the Arbiter's Pendant... With it, you can gain access to the core of the Udumbara.
Tindoiimu: This is the key...
Maeok: No one else can get inside without it... If you hide there, you'll be out of Qing-Feng's reach...
Maeok: Then... just wait for Toyokuni... you can fight back...
Maeok: Not much time left... I'm here to protect you...
Tindoiimu: Why... Why are you doing this?
Maeok: Because you... are the arbiter... Leader of both sides...
Maeok: I trust in the Holy Dragon... in its will... the Arbiter stands for justice... peace...
Tindoiimu: The Holy Dragon...!
Tindoiimu: Your Holy Dragon killed so many of my people! Deaths that you ordered! Where's the justice in that!?
Tindoiimu: If you knew justice at all, you could have stopped all of this so much earlier! You're just as bad as the rest of them!
Maeok: I won't deny that... I won't try to explain myself...
Tindoiimu: I'm not your hostage anymore. You're all going to regret it...
Maeok: So be it... that is fate. New arbiter... brings change...
Maeok: Tindoiimu.
Maeok: I'm... sorry...
Tindoiimu: ......
Assassin: There they are!!
Qing-Feng: Hmph, just can't wait to go down in the history books as a criminal, huh Maeok?
Maeok: Criminal... My only crime is not stopping you earlier.
Maeok: May this spirit water... redeem my wrongdoings...
Qing-Feng: What are you all waiting for!? Get her!
Soohyeon: (Mom... I hope you're at peace...)
Miranda: Master, can you see something in the skies?
Law: No... nothing...
Yan-Bo: ...Eh...
Scared Assassin: Dead... she's finally dead...
Qing-Feng: Wasted enough of my precious time, she did.
Qing-Feng: Yuck. She's dead but still has that damned look in her eyes...
Maeok: Gyaagh!!
Qing-Feng: What in the...!?
Scared Assassin: Yagh! She's alive... She's a... ghost!!
Maeok: Yagh... gungh...
Maeok: (Holy Dragon... I am helpless... Please, watch over the east, protect my daughter...)
Maeok: (Forgive me... I couldn't keep my promise...)
Maeok: (Soohyeon... forgive me...)
